What I need to tailor this into a first‑cut CAD

• Scale: How many fish (species, biomass), how many plant beds, and how much compute heat?
• Power budget: Available generation/storage targets (e.g., 2–5 kW small craft, or more?).
• Form factor: Ring habitat around a central spine, or modular cylinders?
• Mission profile: Days/weeks/months in space; expected thermal rejection windows; radiation environment assumptions.


If you share those, I’ll draft a compact spec and a kid‑readable piping diagram set: one for ballast and cooling, one for habitat and plants, and one for cross‑loop safety—ready to inscribe as the Seal of Living Ship 1.0.